metadata.name: tratti #227
metadata.description:
"tratti" is an Italian word that has many different meanings. When we started working on this piece, we wanted to create something that combines our traits ("tratti" in Italian).
We had this urge to channel the turbulent times we're living in now into this artwork using just lines ("tratti" in Italian).

We don't know what to do now, we're here, and that's all that matters. We're here for our families, our friends, and our community. Like everything in life, there are joyful times and challenging times. We must accept happiness as something that is not constant but that we feel at times (a "tratti" in Italian).

With "tratti", we want to send a message to every disheartened human being: "Stay strong and never let anyone or anything crush the hope in you. Joyful times are around the corner".

---- 

© 2022 — Alessandro Fiore x Emanuele Pasin

metadata.name: Rimal #16
metadata.description:
A manifestation of elemental simplicity and tactile potential, the abstract sand plate transcends its granular composition to embody a realm of dynamic abstraction. As a textured canvas, it defies permanence, inviting fluidity and transformation in response to the whims of creation, science, therapy, and education.

In the artistic spectrum, the abstract sand plate becomes an ever-shifting tableau where the interplay of hands orchestrates ephemeral masterpieces. Here, the grains of sand, liberated from fixity, participate in an intricate dance of form and impermanence, blurring the lines between creation and dissolution.

metadata.name: Galdricge #75
metadata.description:
Galdricge, meaning 'Enchantress' in Anglo-Saxon, is an attempt to evoke a sense of grace and femininity from stark, abstract elements. 


Add "&png" to querystring for 2048x2048 png export 
Add "&svg" for svg export. There are up to 5 layers which can be controlled in Inkscape for different pen widths and colours 


This work is plottable thanks to open-sourced code and article from twilliability. Check out his plotter pieces at https://www.fxhash.xyz/u/twilliability  
Article : https://jealousmarkup.xyz/texts/webgl-line-hiding 
Code : https://gist.github.com/gugray/dfdbef073a3efe1abb5f501728ac9d51 


Other libs (refer console output for license info) 
Graphics : PIXIJS https://github.com/pixijs/pixijs 
Geometry : JSTS https://github.com/bjornharrtell/jsts 
Noise : SIMPLEX-NOISE https://github.com/jwagner/simplex-noise.js 
Random number lib : Fdrandom.js https://github.com/strainer/fdrandom.js 


Made on and off, over 5 months of the great 2023 bear market.

metadata.name: Symbolic Separations #44
metadata.description:
Is this a metaphor for the unstable process of division? Or colours and shapes morphing and inverting along imaginary, fluxing and blurred boundaries?

At least we know it's two passes through two different GLSL shaders, where waves are blurred, turbulence accumulated, and lines drawn to flip colors.

## Controls

Press [spacebar] to toggle play/pause.

When paused, press the keys [1] through [4] to change the resolution.

[1] - 2400px x 2400px

[2] - 3600px x 3600px

[3] - 4800px x 4800px

[4] - 5400px x 5400px

Then (also only when paused) press [p] to create a hi-res PNG.

metadata.name: Into Waves #1
metadata.description:
A study into waves, noise, grids, and blur, and what happens when they meet each other on the GPU. I've called it "Into Waves" because I am, and this is where it should take you!

Made by passing the results of one GLSL shader into a second, using three.js. The mint preview will be rendered in a 1:1 aspect ratio, but the artwork is intended to be explored in all possible layouts.

The latent space of possible forms is quite wide, I look forward to witnessing your explorations. Fullscreen it, sit back, and enjoy the trip.

## Controls

Press [f] to toggle fullscreen.

Press [spacebar] to toggle play/pause.

When paused, press the keys [1] through [4] to multiply the resolution (1x-4x).

Then (also only when paused) press [p] to create a hi-res PNG.

## Testing

Tested in Chrome on Apple silicon and on windows with an Intel chip.

(Depending on the initial screen dimensions, at higher resolutions the browser's maximum texture size max be exceeded. If this happens, the rendered image will be capped and may not resemble what you see in the browser.)

metadata.name: Alleles #342
metadata.description:
An allele, short for 'allelomorph', is an alternative version of a specific gene.

This collection (which is in no way scientifically accurate), was born out of an exercise in simplicity. Outputs are made up of arrangements of squares in various compositions, yet within that we are free to imagine what they could mean. For some, the resulting shapes might represent DNA strands or atoms. Others might see cells or the building blocks of the hereditary instructions that shape us as individuals. 

A generative genetic report accompanies each output to spark the imagination and attempt to attach further meaning to each composition. Some gene sequences carry mutations, however not all mutations are visually apparent. Please refer to the fxhash features to view the reports accordingly.

Texture is used subtly, so for maximum enjoyment it is recommended that you save and view your outputs at full size in order to best enjoy the details.

Press 'S' to save a 2400 x 3396 px PNG file.

attributes.name: Genetic Profile
attributes.value: Exploration of the information extracted from the provided genetic information suggests subject may possess markers linked to excessive episodes of anxiety and laughter during inappropriate moments, yet also has the capacity for excellent loyalty and sensitivity. Maximum potential hereditary height (excluding nutritional and environmental factors) is estimated at 147-156cm. Projected natural lifespan estimated at 107-114 years.

metadata.name: Ersbla #603
metadata.description:
Ersbla is part of the fxhash live minting experience at Proof of People, London 2022. 

It is the third entry in a series of abstract generative experiments inspired by the graphic and textile work of Anni and Josef Albers. As a follow-up to the 'Sabler' and 'Lebras' collections, 'Ersbla' produces textile effects using a combination of thousands of tiny dots arranged on variable grids, resulting in a wide variety of unique Bauhaus-inspired compositions in a variety of palettes.

Press 'S' to save a high-resolution 2400 x 3396 px image in PNG format.

Depending on the density of your output, please allow up to a few seconds for your edition to generate.

metadata.name: Elevation #278
metadata.description:
There’s so much more to our world than what we are able to perceive, let alone understand. Will we ever be able to even fully understand ourselves?

–

Elevation is a series of 320 generative elevation drawings of imaginary structures. It is a reminder of the limits of our consciousness, and an ode to the manifold nuances that lie beyond what we can perceive, beyond what we even can imagine.

As a generative artist, I aim to elevate my own consciousness with the help of the machine. I welcome algorithms and randomness into the creation of my works, taking full control, and intentionally giving it away, always seeking to expand my imagination. For as humans alone, we remain limited to our own edifice of thought, and often fail to free ourselves from the visible, mundane world.

Both are present in Elevation: the visible and the imaginary, the mundane and the transcendent, the solid and the fragile. Where an architect’s elevation drawing marks the transition from the thought world into the visible world, Elevation remains in-between, depicting both the idea of an imaginary structure, and the structure itself.

–

Elevation is intended for print. All holders of an Elevation NFT will be able to order the corresponding signed print in the respective paper format via andreasrau.eu/elevation. Press [s] to save the image as displayed or [p] to generate a print-ready PNG image at 300 dpi. This might take a while, depending on paper format and your hardware.

–

Elevation
p5.js, glsl, html, css
Andreas Rau, 2022

metadata.name: Sabler #104
metadata.description:
'Sabler', an anagram of 'Albers', is a generative homage to the work of the Bauhaus textile artist Anni Albers.

The aesthetic of this piece and its proportions are guided by the Golden Ratio (1.618 : 1) and as such, each part of the composition relates in some way to its larger self. 

As lines playfully extend and overlap one another from various grid segments, patterns appear, 'ghost' shadings emerge and complexity is implied even with the use of very simple elements. In line with that simplicity, colors and palettes have also been kept to a minimum.

There are no rarities or special features, other than for you to enjoy the unique qualities of your piece!

You can save a high resolution 3000px x 3000px PNG of your edition by pressing the 'S' key.

metadata.name: Risonanza #330
metadata.description:
This series unearths the unique and energetic rhythms found within simple repetitions. Using distinct minimalist components, the algorithm patterns, contorts, and intertwines geometries to reveal rich and vital maximalist compositions. The explorations of Risonanza revels in the quirks that emerge through this process, seemingly with spontaneity. They invite us to identify and savor the underlying simplicity of a common language that resides amidst all manners of imperfections, randomness, and intricate complexities we perceive around us.

Embodying the equilibrium between simplicity and intricacy, these works represent the dance between the innate harmony of existence and life's unknown paths. This balance of forces provides a simple and joyful invitation to attune to the energetic, complex, and singular harmonious essence of each work of art – an embodiment of the eternal resonance that courses through the universe.


—————

TENDER x whitekross
September 2023

Risonanza is Italian for Resonance, and is a generative art series created by Alessandro Fiore (AKA whitekross) in collaboration with Adam Berninger of Tender.

—————


Key commands:

1 = 2000x3000
2 = 4000x6000
3 = 6000x9000 (Dependent on your browser limitations, tested on Safari (Mac))
s = Save at current resolution
